<Defs>

  <ThingDef ParentName="ArmorMachineableBase">
    <defName>EOTF_OfficerCarapaceArmor</defName>
    <label>Officer Carapace Armor</label>
    <description>Carapace Armor comes in many shapes and sizes, this variant however was designed in the factories of the Deathworld of Fury. Despite the name, Fury is a highly organized society with a caste system which maintains a highborn nobility and a lowborn servile class. Often under siege by the Insectoid fleets, the Furian Guard is subject to the same stratification as their cities. As the Officers of the Furian Guard are found among the nobility, they have access to this specific armor. Reinforced with additional plasteel and adorned with gold filagree which offers both protection and proof of status.</description>
    <techLevel>Spacer</techLevel>
    <recipeMaker>
      <researchPrerequisite>EOTF_OfficerCarapaceArmor</researchPrerequisite>
      <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedTechArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
      <skillRequirements>
        <Crafting>7</Crafting>
      </skillRequirements>
      <recipeUsers Inherit="False">
        <li>TableMachining</li>
      </recipeUsers>
    </recipeMaker>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Armor/OfficerArmor/OfficerArmor</texPath>
      <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
      <shaderType>CutoutComplex</shaderType>
    </graphicData>
    <statBases>
      <WorkToMake>12000</WorkToMake>
      <MarketValue>1000</MarketValue>
      <MaxHitPoints>265</MaxHitPoints>
      <Mass>10.0</Mass>
      <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>1.15</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
      <EquipDelay>8</EquipDelay>
    </statBases>
    <equippedStatOffsets>
      <MoveSpeed>-0.05</MoveSpeed>
      <SlaveSuppressionOffset MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">-0.2</SlaveSuppressionOffset>
    </equippedStatOffsets>
    <thingCategories>
      <li>EOTF_Armor</li>
    </thingCategories>
    <costList>
      <Cloth>60</Cloth>
      <Plasteel>30</Plasteel>
      <ComponentIndustrial>3</ComponentIndustrial>
    </costList>
    <stuffCategories>
      <li>Metallic</li>
    </stuffCategories>
    <costStuffCount>100</costStuffCount>
    <apparel>
      <bodyPartGroups>
        <li>Torso</li>
        <li>Shoulders</li>
        <li>Neck</li>
      </bodyPartGroups>
      <useWornGraphicMask>True</useWornGraphicMask>
      <layers>
        <li>Middle</li>
      </layers>
      <defaultOutfitTags>
        <li>Soldier</li>
      </defaultOutfitTags>
      <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Armor/OfficerArmor/OfficerArmor</wornGraphicPath>
      <tags Inherit="False">
        <li>EOTF_Armor_Officer</li>
      </tags>
      <renderNodeProperties>
        <li Class="EOTF.Core.DecalSystem.PawnRenderNodePropertiesOmni">
          <nodeClass>EOTF.Core.DecalSystem.PawnRenderNodeDecal</nodeClass>
          <workerClass>EOTF.Core.DecalSystem.PawnRenderNodeWorkerApparel</workerClass>
          <parentTagDef>ApparelBody</parentTagDef>
          <baseLayer>16</baseLayer>
          <texPaths>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Captain</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Crown</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Hawk</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Leaf Cluster</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Lionhead</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/OfficerStar</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/StarBurst</li>
            <li>Things/Decals/Officer/Wreath</li>
          </texPaths>
          <visibleFacing>
            <li>South</li>
            <li>North</li>
          </visibleFacing>
          <drawData>
            <scale>0.120</scale>
            <defaultData>
              <layer>23.555</layer>
              <offset>(0,0,-0.155)</offset>
              <flip>true</flip>
            </defaultData>
            <dataNorth>
              <layer>23.655</layer>
              <offset>(0,0,-0.148)</offset>
            </dataNorth>
            <bodyTypeScales>
              <Hulk>1.35</Hulk>
              <Fat>1.1</Fat>
              <Thin>0.9</Thin>
              <Female>1.05</Female>
            </bodyTypeScales>
          </drawData>
        </li>
      </renderNodeProperties>
    </apparel>
    <comps>
      <li Class="EOTF.Core.DecalSystem.CompPropertiesEditDecalMarker" />
    </comps>
    <colorGenerator Class="ColorGenerator_StandardApparel" />
    <tradeTags>
      <li>Armor</li>
      <li>EOTF_Armor</li>
    </tradeTags>
  </ThingDef>

  <!-- Scout Armor and Variants-->
  <ThingDef ParentName="ArmorMachineableBase">
    <defName>EOTF_ScoutCarapaceArmor</defName>
    <label>Scout Carapace Armor</label>
    <description>The most important part of any army is the ability to acquire intelligence on their enemies. The Vanguard Carapace Armor was designed on several planets though the most famous and its namesake would be by the Alexandrian Vanguard. During the First War of Alexandria against the Mechanoids, the most important factor in combat was speed. While not being heavy standard Carapace Armor is bulky and could be lightened. The Vanguard did so through removal of the shoulder plates and the “shaving” of certain areas until it only protected the chest of the wearer.</description>
    <techLevel>Spacer</techLevel>
    <recipeMaker>
      <researchPrerequisite>EOTF_CarapaceArmor</researchPrerequisite>
      <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedTechArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
      <skillRequirements>
        <Crafting>5</Crafting>
      </skillRequirements>
